IT is ordered, and Col: Ienens Lev
                  •
               : general Buchly and Maior brittayne are hereby deſired and appointed to veiw all the horſes with in this Garriſon and that they take particular notcie of all ſuch hoeſes as aee fit to be killed for beefe, for proviſions for the Garriſon, and that they give an account of theire doeings herein to morrow at two of the clock in the after-noone unto the Governour and Councell;
